data.enText: a sea creature with a hard shell, a long body divided into sections, eight legs and two large claws (= curved and pointed arms for catching and holding things). Its shell is black but turns bright red when it is boiled.
meat from a lobster , used for food

tr: any of several edible marine crustaceans of the families Homaridae and Nephropsidae and Palinuridae

value.def: A lobster is a sea creature that has a hard shell, two large claws, and eight legs.

example.ex: She sold me a couple of live lobsters.
example.tran: 她卖了几只活龙虾给我。

posc.def: Lobster is the flesh of a lobster eaten as food.

example.ex: ...lobster on a bed of fresh vegetables.
example.tran: 放在一层新鲜蔬菜上的龙虾肉
